`lifecycle/` is the full three-phase orchestration for a single caged `claude` run: prepare (validate, mint rundir, materialize bind files), run (proxy + bwrap exec via `run/`), teardown (best-effort cleanup). Depending on this directory gets you `execute(r: &Resolved) -> Result<RunOutcome, CageError>`, the single public entry point; everything else here is internal machinery feeding that call.

`Resolved` (mod.rs) is the shared input struct threaded through all three phases ‚Äî target root, mode, tool paths, and `.cagevars`-derived extra env (from `cagevars.rs`). `env.rs` builds the container environment (`cage_env`) from `Resolved` and enforces `NEVER_OVERRIDABLE` keys can't be clobbered by `.cagevars` passthrough ‚Äî a change in what `cagevars.rs` returns must stay compatible with that rejection list. `prepare.rs` produces `Prep` (rundir, claude runtime, mask/rules/resolv files); `run.rs` consumes `Prep` to exec bwrap and produce `RunOutcome`; `teardown.rs` consumes `Prep` last, deleting only `prep.rundir`. This prepare‚Üírun‚Üíteardown handoff via `Prep` is the core coupling ‚Äî changing `Prep`'s shape means touching all three files plus whatever `run/` mounts from it.

Billed-mode gating is cross-cutting: `prepare.rs` requires a clean git tree and resolves `ClaudeRuntime` only when `mode_is_billed`; `run.rs` only starts the proxy/relay in billed modes; `env.rs` only adds `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` (never the API key ‚Äî auth is passthrough OAuth) in billed modes. Non-billed modes skip all three consistently.

Invariant spanning the subtree: diagnostics (proxy log, teardown errors) never affect `RunOutcome`'s exit code (ADR-027) ‚Äî only `prepare`/`run` errors propagate from `execute`; teardown always runs and always swallows errors.

`run/` is the detailed run-phase pipeline (preflight, PTY, bwrap invocation); see its own rollup.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so no divergence check is possible.